    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-06T16:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-06T16:40:00-05:00" n="842"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d842">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">836.48 1930 Hurricane/15: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-06T17:00:00-04:40"
                            >September 6, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>98. Department’s 42, September 5, 6 p.m. Following is local committee: Morgan of
                    City Bank, chairman, Davidson of Electric Company, British Chargé, Haitian
                    Minister, French Chargé, Spanish Chargé, Lopez Aneiro of Porto Rican Colony,
                    self, and Clark ex officio.</p>
                <p>Three relief boats off port, another due, and two or more coming Monday. Porto
                    Rican medical unit has landed. River rapidly falling and should be available for
                    landing cargo within twenty-four hours if launches can be obtained. Squadron of
                    planes has just flown over, presumably with medical supplies from
                    Port-au-Prince. Road to Boano opened and roads to Macoris and Azua reported
                    practicable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
